    "result": {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Becky's Cookbook"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"a1fb171a-76d5-5169-ad74-8e6b35fa29a3","excerpt":"I’m very excited to write my first recipie today!! For today’s fish curry recipe we’ll be using king fish! But this recipe can be used for other fish like…","html":"<p>I’m very excited to write my first recipie today!!</p>\n<p>For today’s fish curry recipe we’ll be using king fish! But this recipe can be used for other fish like pomfret.</p>\n<h3>Ingredients requried:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Chilly powder 2 teaspoon</em></li>\n<li><em>Corriander powder 2 teaspoon</em></li>\n<li><em>Turmeric powder 1 teaspoon</em></li>\n<li><em>Jeera 3 spoons</em></li>\n<li><em>Garlic🧄 4 pods</em></li>\n<li><em>Tamarind water</em></li>\n<li><em>Salt</em></li>\n<li><em>Grated coconut 🥥 5 spoons</em></li>\n<li><em>Tomato 🍅 - 1</em></li>\n<li><em>Curry Leaves 🍃-2 strings</em></li>\n<li><em>Shallots (smallonions) 🧅 - 10-12 pieces</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/cookbook/static/83c2ac4fab33162ced8538faa2d0a9b8/e5166/fish-curry.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Fish Curry\"\n        title=\"Fish Curry\"\n        src=\"/cookbook/static/83c2ac4fab33162ced8538faa2d0a9b8/828fb/fish-curry.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/cookbook/static/83c2ac4fab33162ced8538faa2d0a9b8/ff44c/fish-curry.jpg 158w,\n/cookbook/static/83c2ac4fab33162ced8538faa2d0a9b8/a6688/fish-curry.jpg 315w,\n/cookbook/static/83c2ac4fab33162ced8538faa2d0a9b8/828fb/fish-curry.jpg 630w,\n/cookbook/static/83c2ac4fab33162ced8538faa2d0a9b8/0ede0/fish-curry.jpg 945w,\n/cookbook/static/83c2ac4fab33162ced8538faa2d0a9b8/e5166/fish-curry.jpg 1200w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3>Steps to cook:</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Soak lemon sized tamarind in one cup of water.</li>\n<li>In a blender, add grated coconut, shallots(10-12 pieces), curry leaves(2 strings), jeera, chilly powder, corriander powder, turmeric powder, garlic, 1 cup water and blend it until it becomes a finely grinded paste.</li>\n<li>In a pan, add the grinded mixture and heat it until it boils.</li>\n<li>Put the fish into the pan when the mixture boils.</li>\n<li>Immediately add the tamarind water.</li>\n<li>Add some curry leaves and a finely chopped tomato.</li>\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\n<li>Let the fish curry boil for around 15 minutes.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Finally, you’re tasty fish curry is ready. You can serve it with rice 🍚and some vegetables 🍲.\nStay tuned for more recipes…😊 👩‍🍳</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Fish Curry","date":"December 04, 2021","description":"Our yummy fish curry recipe."}},"previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/fish-curry copy/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Fish Curry"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"a1fb171a-76d5-5169-ad74-8e6b35fa29a3","previousPostId":null,"nextPostId":"5f625a66-7c40-5b66-929e-1b10137d2ec4"}},
